WEBVTT

00:01.839 --> 00:04.507
(Finch) We are being watched.

00:04.509 --> 00:06.643
The government has a secret system...

00:06.645 --> 00:10.948
a machine that spies on you
every hour of every day.

00:10.950 --> 00:13.617
I designed the machine
to detect acts of terror,

00:13.619 --> 00:15.452
but it sees everything...

00:15.454 --> 00:18.854
Violent crimes involving ordinary people.

00:18.856 --> 00:21.857
The government considers
these people irrelevant.

00:21.859 --> 00:23.859
We don't.

00:23.861 --> 00:28.465
Hunted by the authorities,
we work in secret.

00:28.467 --> 00:30.300
You will never find us.

00:30.302 --> 00:32.366
But victim or perpetrator,

00:32.369 --> 00:35.404
if your number's up, we'll find you.

00:35.805 --> 00:38.805
Synced and corrected by<font color=#009900> OussLP</font>
- www.addic7ed.com

00:39.943 --> 00:41.276
We are only numbers to it.

00:41.278 --> 00:43.112
No. The Machine cares about us.

00:43.114 --> 00:44.780
The second that a bullet enters your brain,

00:44.782 --> 00:47.816
the Machine will cast
you off and replace you.

00:47.818 --> 00:49.050
(Elias) I want them to release you.

00:49.052 --> 00:52.488
I just want it to be done.

00:52.490 --> 00:53.822
Okay, Anthony.

00:53.824 --> 00:56.125
[electronics beeping]

00:56.127 --> 00:57.692
[explosion booms]

00:57.694 --> 00:59.728
(Finch) If you better understood Samaritan,

00:59.730 --> 01:01.330
you would know it employs a private army

01:01.332 --> 01:02.664
to do its bidding.

01:02.666 --> 01:04.397
You would suspect they would employ

01:04.400 --> 01:08.803
at least one of them as a spy
in your own organization.

01:09.804 --> 01:10.804
_

01:14.343 --> 01:15.677
[phone line rings]

01:15.679 --> 01:17.478
(Dennis) Hey, hon. Are you at work?

01:17.480 --> 01:19.981
(Shelly) Not yet. My
morning has been hellish.

01:19.983 --> 01:22.583
Oh, Jackson forgot his lunch again today.

01:22.585 --> 01:24.352
But you know what, he
can eat cafeteria food,

01:24.354 --> 01:26.354
because I have got a ton of papers to grade

01:26.356 --> 01:28.356
before second period.

01:28.358 --> 01:30.691
[tense music]

01:30.693 --> 01:32.226
Oh, my God.

01:32.228 --> 01:34.128
My brakes aren't working. My brakes!

01:34.130 --> 01:35.296
(Dennis) What? What do you mean?

01:35.298 --> 01:36.297
[tires squeal]

01:36.299 --> 01:37.631
Dennis!

01:37.633 --> 01:40.233
[screams]

01:40.235 --> 01:41.131
[metallic crash]

01:41.250 --> 01:43.132
_

01:43.438 --> 01:47.641
♪

01:47.643 --> 01:49.509
[car door clicks]

01:49.511 --> 01:51.712
♪ ♪

01:51.714 --> 01:54.981
[groans, yells weakly]

01:54.983 --> 01:58.585
♪

01:58.587 --> 02:00.887
(Control) Get the body.

02:00.889 --> 02:07.727
♪

02:07.729 --> 02:10.096
[device beeping]

02:10.098 --> 02:11.831
♪ ♪

02:11.833 --> 02:14.200
All good, ma'am. Right on schedule.

02:14.202 --> 02:15.735
Drive.

02:15.737 --> 02:18.805
♪

02:18.807 --> 02:21.941
[explosion booms]

02:21.943 --> 02:24.711
[dramatic music]

02:24.713 --> 02:27.580
♪

02:33.486 --> 02:35.554
[solemn music]

02:35.556 --> 02:36.855
You look like hell.

02:36.857 --> 02:39.024
Good to see you too, Lionel.

02:39.026 --> 02:40.992
Maybe next time you decide
to take on a psychopath

02:40.994 --> 02:43.528
in the frozen Tundra, you'll
call your partner first.

02:43.530 --> 02:47.065
Hey. You're right.

02:47.067 --> 02:51.236
You're a good detective,
and a damn good friend.

02:51.238 --> 02:53.171
You have a temperature or something?

02:53.173 --> 02:54.973
I'm still standing...

02:54.975 --> 02:58.676
which is more than I can
say for our friends here.

02:58.678 --> 03:00.211
(Fusco) Brotherhood soldier.

03:00.213 --> 03:02.380
Elias's guy came out of nowhere,

03:02.382 --> 03:04.515
shot Dominic's boys, and disappeared.

03:04.517 --> 03:06.284
(Fusco) It's like deja vu all over again.

03:06.286 --> 03:08.686
Lionel, tell me this.

03:08.688 --> 03:11.456
How did a gunman get through security?

03:11.458 --> 03:15.011
That's a good question, Detective.

03:16.295 --> 03:18.629
Finch, I got four dead
Brotherhood soldiers.

03:18.631 --> 03:21.398
(Reese) Why didn't the Machine give
us any of their numbers this time?

03:21.400 --> 03:22.733
I wish I knew.

03:22.735 --> 03:24.401
Though it's no stretch to imagine

03:24.403 --> 03:26.703
that a cunning fugitive like
Elias might have found

03:26.705 --> 03:29.373
a way to communicate that
even the Machine can't trace.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.041
At least that's one theory.

03:31.043 --> 03:32.576
You got another?

03:32.578 --> 03:35.746
Samaritan has found the Machine.

03:35.748 --> 03:38.214
If that were true, we'd all be dead.

03:38.216 --> 03:39.983
What happened, Ms. Groves?

03:39.985 --> 03:43.887
♪

03:43.889 --> 03:47.791
Turns out the People's
Republic is surprisingly lax

03:47.793 --> 03:50.994
on full-body searches.

03:50.996 --> 03:52.728
♪

03:52.730 --> 03:54.898
How goes your gang war, Harry?

03:54.900 --> 03:57.167
Dangerous.

03:57.169 --> 03:59.502
I'm afraid it's only a matter of time

03:59.504 --> 04:01.771
before Dominic retaliates.

04:01.773 --> 04:04.941
[phone ringing]

04:04.943 --> 04:07.510
Might be sooner than you think.

04:07.512 --> 04:11.079
[tense music]

04:11.081 --> 04:12.615
[The Machine reciting numbers]

04:12.617 --> 04:14.016
You getting this number, Finch?

04:14.018 --> 04:16.652
It's actually two numbers, Mr. Reese.

04:16.654 --> 04:19.087
Dominic and Elias.

04:19.089 --> 04:20.456
It seem the two crime bosses

04:20.458 --> 04:21.990
are hell-bent on killing each other.

04:21.992 --> 04:23.625
God only knows how many innocent victims

04:23.627 --> 04:25.093
will get caught in the crossfire.

04:25.095 --> 04:28.864
We have to find a way to
stop this war, Mr. Reese.

04:28.866 --> 04:30.265
Got a feeling this might help.

04:30.267 --> 04:31.633
[camera shutter snaps]

04:31.635 --> 04:33.768
(Finch) Hmm, it's some sort of canister.

04:33.770 --> 04:35.137
I'll look into that.

04:35.139 --> 04:37.639
In the meantime, I've managed to trace

04:37.641 --> 04:40.274
the Brotherhood's security transport trucks

04:40.276 --> 04:41.810
to a new location.

04:41.812 --> 04:44.379
Thanks. I'll take Lionel.

04:44.381 --> 04:47.951
♪

04:48.352 --> 04:49.352
_

04:49.453 --> 04:51.953
[indistinct chatter]

04:51.955 --> 04:58.492
♪

04:58.494 --> 04:59.894
(Link) We got a problem.

04:59.896 --> 05:01.829
Boys want retribution for the courthouse.

05:01.831 --> 05:03.998
And they'll have it in due time.

05:04.000 --> 05:05.733
Time's running out.

05:05.735 --> 05:08.302
We got soldiers with itchy trigger fingers.

05:08.304 --> 05:10.171
Looks like there's trouble in paradise.

05:10.173 --> 05:12.239
We need to take action.

05:14.308 --> 05:16.677
You and me, we go back a long time.

05:16.679 --> 05:20.313
Remember that skinny
pockmarked kid from Trinidad?

05:20.315 --> 05:22.983
You told him it's not enough to hit back.

05:22.985 --> 05:26.186
No, you need to put your
enemy in the ground.

05:26.188 --> 05:29.356
I haven't forgotten.

05:29.358 --> 05:32.092
Only one way this war ends.

05:32.094 --> 05:36.562
♪

05:36.564 --> 05:37.998
[camera shutter snaps]

05:38.000 --> 05:39.532
Brotherhood's preparing for battle.

05:39.534 --> 05:42.335
- Increased security, patrols.
- Mr. Reese?

05:42.337 --> 05:43.904
I was thinking that you and Detective Fusco

05:43.906 --> 05:45.271
might stop by the bank.

05:45.273 --> 05:47.339
You need us to make a deposit, Finch?

05:47.341 --> 05:49.375
The canister from the crime scene

05:49.377 --> 05:53.679
is a remnant of a long-defunct
pneumatic tube mail network

05:53.681 --> 05:55.214
that once ran beneath the city.

05:55.216 --> 05:58.217
One of its hubs was an old retail bank

05:58.219 --> 06:00.853
which has recently found new ownership.

06:00.855 --> 06:03.055
- Carl Elias?
- Indeed.

06:03.057 --> 06:05.291
Mr. Elias appears to have revived it

06:05.293 --> 06:07.359
to conceal his communications.

06:07.361 --> 06:08.794
And smuggle murder weapons

06:08.796 --> 06:11.196
into highly secured government buildings.

06:11.198 --> 06:13.598
(Reese) If Elias is at the
bank, we'll find him.

06:13.600 --> 06:15.234
[phone ringing]

06:15.236 --> 06:18.303
[dramatic music]

06:18.305 --> 06:20.171
♪

06:20.173 --> 06:22.273
Shaw's phone.

06:22.275 --> 06:24.309
- Finch?
- I have to go, Mr. Reese.

06:24.311 --> 06:26.545
(Finch) You'll have to
manage Elias yourself.

06:26.547 --> 06:29.213
♪

06:29.215 --> 06:30.281
Hello?

06:30.283 --> 06:31.616
(Shaw) Root, are you there?

06:31.618 --> 06:33.217
It's me. I need your help.

06:33.219 --> 06:34.218
[line clicks]

06:34.220 --> 06:36.654
Shaw?

06:36.656 --> 06:38.622
Wait. Sameen.

06:38.624 --> 06:39.924
♪

06:41.000 --> 06:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:50.318 --> 06:52.420
[tense music]

06:52.421 --> 06:54.921
_

06:55.051 --> 07:01.227
♪

07:01.229 --> 07:03.997
[gasps]

07:03.999 --> 07:07.133
W-where am I?

07:07.135 --> 07:08.734
Why are you doing this?

07:08.736 --> 07:11.570
We need to talk about Samaritan.

07:11.572 --> 07:14.540
I don't... I don't know what that means.

07:14.542 --> 07:17.743
♪

07:17.745 --> 07:21.213
You know Tyler, don't you, Shelly?

07:21.215 --> 07:24.182
What? N-no.

07:24.184 --> 07:25.317
I don't know that man.

07:25.319 --> 07:29.922
He was one of my best agents.

07:29.924 --> 07:31.790
It's your last chance to say good-bye.

07:31.792 --> 07:34.159
[inhales sharply] No.

07:34.161 --> 07:35.794
Please don't...

07:35.796 --> 07:36.929
(Shelly) No.

07:36.931 --> 07:37.963
[gunshot]

07:37.965 --> 07:40.698
Oh, no! No!

07:40.700 --> 07:43.568
How could you forget a face like that?

07:43.570 --> 07:45.970
[crying] I don't understand.

07:45.972 --> 07:48.606
♪

07:48.608 --> 07:51.042
Why are you doing this?

07:51.044 --> 07:56.013
I want you to be helpful.

07:56.015 --> 07:58.082
Tyler was helpful.

07:58.084 --> 07:59.183
At first.

07:59.185 --> 08:00.551
He admitted to being

08:00.553 --> 08:02.619
one of several Samaritan moles

08:02.621 --> 08:04.956
embedded in the ISA.

08:04.958 --> 08:08.926
He admitted that you were their handler.

08:08.928 --> 08:12.830
I'm just a teacher and a mom.

08:12.832 --> 08:16.132
I just... I just want to
go home to my family.

08:16.134 --> 08:17.400
(Control) I understand.

08:17.402 --> 08:19.169
I'm a mother too.

08:19.171 --> 08:22.439
♪

08:22.441 --> 08:24.875
That's why I'm giving you one last chance

08:24.877 --> 08:27.778
to save your own life.

08:27.780 --> 08:30.647
Tell the truth, Shelly.

08:30.649 --> 08:33.866
Or you too...

08:34.919 --> 08:37.386
will end up a spot on the wall.

08:37.389 --> 08:40.423
♪

08:40.424 --> 08:41.756
(Shaw) Root, are you there?

08:41.759 --> 08:43.126
It's me. I need your help.

08:43.128 --> 08:44.126
[phone rings]

08:44.129 --> 08:48.230
[solemn music]

08:48.232 --> 08:50.332
She's alive, Harold.

08:50.334 --> 08:52.768
We wrote her off for dead, but she's alive.

08:52.770 --> 08:54.103
We don't know that, Ms. Groves.

08:54.105 --> 08:55.104
Except we do.

08:55.106 --> 08:56.472
I just talked to her

08:56.474 --> 08:59.141
on a call originating from the city.

08:59.143 --> 09:02.177
♪

09:02.179 --> 09:05.180
Can we take just five minutes
and talk this through?

09:05.182 --> 09:07.349
The last time we had this conversation,

09:07.351 --> 09:09.451
I actually listened to you.

09:09.453 --> 09:12.621
And to the Machine.

09:12.623 --> 09:14.123
I called off my search,

09:14.125 --> 09:15.524
and all this time,

09:15.526 --> 09:17.859
she needed us, Harold.

09:17.861 --> 09:20.162
Like she needs us now.

09:20.164 --> 09:21.997
Isn't this your specialty?

09:21.999 --> 09:24.065
Helping people when the phone rings?

09:24.067 --> 09:26.601
That call was most certainly a trap.

09:26.603 --> 09:27.836
I know.

09:27.838 --> 09:29.337
But Sameen's still alive,

09:29.339 --> 09:31.606
and I'm going after her.

09:31.608 --> 09:34.676
[tense music]

09:34.678 --> 09:39.547
♪

09:39.549 --> 09:41.249
(Finch) I can't help you, Ms. Groves,

09:41.251 --> 09:44.385
if you insist on this impossible pace.

09:44.387 --> 09:46.854
Root. What are we doing out here?

09:46.856 --> 09:48.856
♪

09:48.858 --> 09:52.893
When you told me to stop
looking for Shaw, I did.

09:52.895 --> 09:55.663
But now I need you to help me.

09:55.665 --> 09:58.065
I can't do this alone.

09:58.067 --> 10:01.001
♪

10:01.003 --> 10:02.335
Oh, dear.

10:02.337 --> 10:05.138
Harold taught you blackjack and chess...

10:05.140 --> 10:09.109
♪

10:09.111 --> 10:10.510
But I wonder if he ever taught you

10:10.512 --> 10:12.546
how to play chicken.

10:12.548 --> 10:16.216
♪

10:16.218 --> 10:18.552
I'm gonna walk across this
ledge with my eyes closed

10:18.554 --> 10:22.089
until A, you help me find Sameen,

10:22.091 --> 10:26.059
or B, I fall tragically to my death.

10:26.061 --> 10:30.229
♪

10:30.231 --> 10:33.399
[wind gusting]

10:33.401 --> 10:34.901
- [gasps]
- Ms. Groves.

10:34.903 --> 10:37.889
♪

10:40.193 --> 10:41.808
You've calculated the wind speed,

10:41.810 --> 10:45.611
so you know how treacherous this is.

10:45.613 --> 10:48.247
[beeping] _

10:48.249 --> 10:51.850
You have to ask yourself what's worse:

10:51.852 --> 10:55.621
The two of us working together,

10:55.623 --> 10:58.924
or me taking this next step alone.

10:58.926 --> 11:03.528
♪

11:03.530 --> 11:07.430
[beeping] _

11:09.168 --> 11:12.403
♪

11:12.405 --> 11:15.540
Thanks for playing.

11:15.542 --> 11:16.741
Come on, Harry.

11:16.743 --> 11:18.543
[siren wailing]

11:18.545 --> 11:21.446
She found us a ride.

11:21.448 --> 11:23.414
(Root) The Machine's located Sameen.

11:23.416 --> 11:24.982
Buckle up.

11:31.524 --> 11:33.724
(Root) Shaw's call
originated from a landline

11:33.726 --> 11:35.526
somewhere inside that asylum.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.895
Steiner Psychiatric Institute.

11:37.897 --> 11:41.365
(Root) State controlled with
a closed security system,

11:41.367 --> 11:43.701
which explains our little pit stop.

11:43.703 --> 11:47.404
[tense music]

11:47.406 --> 11:48.706
The Machine would never let us

11:48.708 --> 11:50.974
show up empty-handed to a rescue mission.

11:50.976 --> 11:52.742
♪

11:52.744 --> 11:54.311
Did the Machine have any thoughts about

11:54.313 --> 11:56.713
us not getting ourselves killed?

11:56.715 --> 12:00.917
Right now, she's pretty
fixated on this shovel.

12:00.919 --> 12:04.359
♪

12:04.530 --> 12:05.360
_

12:08.393 --> 12:11.260
This looks like the spot.

12:11.262 --> 12:12.829
You got a plan to get in, partner?

12:12.831 --> 12:14.798
Relax. We got a backstage pass.

12:14.800 --> 12:17.934
♪

12:17.936 --> 12:19.268
We need a word with your boss.

12:19.270 --> 12:20.904
What makes you think he's here?

12:20.906 --> 12:23.105
How 'bout we come back with a SWAT team?

12:23.107 --> 12:27.643
♪ ♪

12:27.645 --> 12:30.279
That's what I thought.

12:30.281 --> 12:31.614
We're in the bank, Finch.

12:31.616 --> 12:33.916
John, I may have to go offline for a while.

12:33.918 --> 12:36.652
(Finch) We've found Sameen.

12:36.654 --> 12:39.088
Shaw? She's alive?

12:39.090 --> 12:42.758
Text me the address. I'm on my way.

12:42.760 --> 12:44.459
I need you to babysit Elias.

12:44.461 --> 12:47.462
(Elias) I don't need a sitter, John.

12:47.464 --> 12:49.564
And I warned you not to interfere.

12:49.566 --> 12:53.802
♪ ♪

12:53.804 --> 12:56.671
By "interfering," you
mean saving your life?

12:56.673 --> 12:58.206
Again?

12:58.208 --> 13:00.475
Who says I need saving?

13:00.477 --> 13:02.510
How long do you think you
got before the Brotherhood

13:02.512 --> 13:04.279
comes looking to make their own withdrawal?

13:04.281 --> 13:06.781
[air whooshes]

13:06.783 --> 13:08.182
Pneumatic tubes once looped around

13:08.184 --> 13:10.285
the entire island of Manhattan

13:10.287 --> 13:12.286
delivering mail and money.

13:12.288 --> 13:14.956
American ingenuity at its finest.

13:14.958 --> 13:16.791
And you would have me leave?

13:16.793 --> 13:18.559
Flee like a coward?

13:18.561 --> 13:19.961
You know me better than that, John.

13:19.963 --> 13:22.130
I know you used to be careful.

13:22.132 --> 13:24.832
Canister in the trash? Sloppy.

13:24.834 --> 13:26.634
And enough evidence to charge you

13:26.636 --> 13:28.402
with conspiracy to commit murder.

13:28.404 --> 13:30.304
Are you placing me under
arrest, Detectives?

13:30.306 --> 13:31.505
If you don't go quietly.

13:31.507 --> 13:32.506
[guns cocking]

13:32.508 --> 13:34.508
Time to end this war.

13:34.510 --> 13:35.876
[gun cocks]

13:35.878 --> 13:38.512
This is your last chance, Detectives.

13:38.514 --> 13:40.347
Walk away while you still can.

13:40.349 --> 13:42.249
[gunfire]

13:42.251 --> 13:44.151
(Reese) The Brotherhood.

13:44.153 --> 13:45.986
Can't say I didn't warn you.

13:45.988 --> 13:47.320
Hurry.

13:47.322 --> 13:50.690
[gunfire and shouting]

13:50.692 --> 13:51.992
You got another way out?

13:51.994 --> 13:53.226
Just like old times.

13:53.228 --> 13:54.727
This way.

13:54.729 --> 13:56.196
♪

13:56.198 --> 13:58.932
Fool me once, old man.

14:12.009 --> 14:15.477
[tense music]

14:15.479 --> 14:17.947
11 weeks ago, this second-rate facility

14:17.949 --> 14:20.016
upgraded to a fiber-optics network

14:20.018 --> 14:22.184
it can't possibly afford.

14:22.186 --> 14:30.058
♪

14:31.628 --> 14:34.696
(Root) Come on, Harry.

14:34.698 --> 14:36.498
♪

14:36.500 --> 14:38.800
Information travels through optical fiber

14:38.802 --> 14:40.468
in pulses of light.

14:40.470 --> 14:43.071
Just 1% of any one pulse contains...

14:43.073 --> 14:45.506
100% of the data.

14:45.508 --> 14:49.110
Like a drop of blood carrying DNA.

14:49.112 --> 14:51.245
Exactly.

14:51.247 --> 14:53.982
Our micro-clamping friend here

14:53.984 --> 14:57.518
will bend the cable just
enough to leak a little light.

14:57.520 --> 15:02.156
And they'll never know they've been hacked.

15:02.158 --> 15:04.192
This is a cascade of information.

15:04.194 --> 15:06.093
Samaritan is doing more than

15:06.095 --> 15:07.895
just harboring Ms. Shaw in there.

15:07.897 --> 15:11.699
We'll need to crack its
considerable encryption.

15:11.701 --> 15:13.701
She's already accessing your laptop.

15:13.703 --> 15:17.437
[laptop beeping]

15:17.439 --> 15:19.006
(Root) "All forces on alert.

15:19.008 --> 15:20.841
We will soon isolate the Machine."

15:20.843 --> 15:25.179
♪

15:25.181 --> 15:28.281
They're close to finding you.

15:28.283 --> 15:31.918
I don't care what happens to me.

15:31.920 --> 15:33.453
(Finch) What did the Machine tell you?

15:33.455 --> 15:35.722
She says it's too dangerous.

15:35.724 --> 15:38.458
I'm inclined to agree, Ms. Groves.

15:38.460 --> 15:42.128
This isn't just a rescue
mission to save Shaw.

15:42.130 --> 15:45.398
The Machine needs our help too.

15:45.400 --> 15:47.433
If we don't save them, who will?

15:47.435 --> 15:49.736
♪

15:52.773 --> 15:56.743
♪

15:56.745 --> 15:59.779
Detective, looks like you caught
a bullet through the shoulder.

15:59.781 --> 16:01.580
Props to the shooter.

16:01.582 --> 16:04.283
Oh, he's dead.

16:04.285 --> 16:06.985
You'll be joining him soon enough.

16:06.987 --> 16:11.823
♪

16:11.825 --> 16:14.226
(Dominic) Extra cell.

16:14.228 --> 16:16.161
Let me guess.

16:16.163 --> 16:18.564
Belongs to our friend Riley.

16:18.566 --> 16:20.565
Fake cop needs one for his day job

16:20.567 --> 16:23.268
and one for special assignments.

16:23.270 --> 16:24.936
What're we waiting for?

16:24.938 --> 16:27.072
We should put Elias down
now while we have the chance.

16:27.074 --> 16:29.975
Tell me, how do Elias and his buddies

16:29.977 --> 16:31.442
manage to stay one step ahead?

16:31.444 --> 16:33.178
They got good intel.

16:33.180 --> 16:36.847
We kill them now, that
intel dies with them.

16:36.849 --> 16:40.084
This isn't just about running the city.

16:40.086 --> 16:42.853
This is about staying alive
long enough to enjoy it.

16:42.855 --> 16:48.092
♪

16:48.094 --> 16:49.594
What do the Romans say?

16:49.596 --> 16:52.930
I came, I saw, I conquered.

16:52.932 --> 16:54.765
You can't conquer what
you don't understand.

16:54.767 --> 16:56.033
(Dominic) Exactly.

16:56.035 --> 16:58.368
In this day and age, a fugitive crime lord

16:58.370 --> 17:01.205
like yourself remains free.

17:01.207 --> 17:02.873
How?

17:02.875 --> 17:06.944
Because two of New York's
finest protect and serve you.

17:06.945 --> 17:08.944
At least they used to.

17:08.946 --> 17:11.381
(Dominic) From now on, they answer to me.

17:11.383 --> 17:12.848
And you're all gonna tell me how

17:12.851 --> 17:16.787
this little symbiotic relationship works.

17:16.789 --> 17:20.056
♪

17:20.058 --> 17:22.792
How are we gonna know
they're telling the truth?

17:22.795 --> 17:27.563
That's why I invited a mutual friend.

17:27.565 --> 17:28.898
Sorry, boys...

17:28.900 --> 17:32.035
♪

17:32.037 --> 17:34.804
But I got an offer I couldn't refuse.

17:34.806 --> 17:38.141
♪

17:42.346 --> 17:43.776
[tense music]

17:45.983 --> 17:49.151
You admitted me to the funny farm once.

17:49.153 --> 17:50.986
Turnabout's fair play.

17:50.988 --> 17:53.322
I don't recall dressing you
like a homeless dope fiend.

17:53.324 --> 17:55.358
[chuckles softly] It's not that bad.

17:55.360 --> 17:57.893
You look more hipster than homeless.

17:57.895 --> 18:01.263
Did the Machine have
any instructions for me?

18:01.265 --> 18:04.132
She said just be honest.

18:04.134 --> 18:06.835
Hello, Doctor?

18:06.837 --> 18:08.603
I need to admit this man on a TDO.

18:08.605 --> 18:10.339
72-hour involuntary hold.

18:10.341 --> 18:13.175
He's an increasingly dangerous
paranoid schizophrenic.

18:13.177 --> 18:16.344
Unless he'd care to disagree?

18:16.346 --> 18:22.717
♪

18:22.719 --> 18:26.388
It's not paranoia if they're
really out to get you.

18:26.390 --> 18:29.056
Who exactly is after you?

18:29.058 --> 18:32.126
The Brotherhood, the federal government,

18:32.128 --> 18:35.429
an artificial super
intelligence, obviously.

18:35.431 --> 18:36.697
What's your name, sir?

18:36.699 --> 18:38.599
I go by many names,

18:38.601 --> 18:40.801
all derived from species of birds.

18:40.803 --> 18:44.438
I'd mark him as a John Doe.

18:44.440 --> 18:46.974
He basically lives in the subway.

18:46.976 --> 18:49.910
Thanks. We'll take it from here.

18:49.912 --> 18:52.312
Everything's gonna be okay. Find Lenny.

18:52.314 --> 18:54.448
Tell him they stole his spaceman.

18:54.450 --> 18:57.751
♪

19:00.354 --> 19:08.261
♪

19:08.263 --> 19:10.496
I hate to interrupt this
scintillating contest,

19:10.498 --> 19:12.465
but I was hoping to find Lenny?

19:12.467 --> 19:18.939
♪

19:18.941 --> 19:21.474
Thank you.

19:23.076 --> 19:26.178
Pardon me. Lenny?

19:26.180 --> 19:28.548
Those gentlemen stole your spaceman.

19:28.550 --> 19:36.456
♪

19:39.426 --> 19:41.026
Liars.

19:41.028 --> 19:42.027
[woman screams]

19:42.029 --> 19:43.862
You stole my spacemen.

19:43.864 --> 19:47.466
[Lenny yelling]

19:47.468 --> 19:49.301
[shouting]

19:49.303 --> 19:50.702
(man) Calm down, calm down.

19:50.704 --> 19:53.672
♪

19:53.674 --> 19:55.373
- No!
- Aah!

19:55.375 --> 19:58.443
[grunting]

19:58.445 --> 19:59.845
♪

19:59.847 --> 20:02.914
[shouting]

20:02.916 --> 20:10.054
♪

20:10.056 --> 20:12.623
The ninth floor is reserved
for the most violent patients.

20:12.625 --> 20:14.625
It's the most secure,
and it's the only floor

20:14.627 --> 20:16.627
without surveillance cameras.

20:16.629 --> 20:20.898
It's also the only floor
with secure elevator access.

20:20.900 --> 20:22.300
This has to be it.

20:22.302 --> 20:24.335
I'm searching the electronic charts

20:24.337 --> 20:26.471
for a profile that might match Sameen's.

20:26.473 --> 20:29.540
[suspenseful music]

20:29.542 --> 20:32.376
♪

20:32.378 --> 20:33.978
Okay, don't lose your head, Ms. Groves.

20:33.980 --> 20:35.713
This might mean nothing,

20:35.715 --> 20:40.384
but they're holding a compact
Persian sociopath in Room 914.

20:40.386 --> 20:43.920
♪

20:43.922 --> 20:45.389
[keypad beeping]

20:45.391 --> 20:49.059
♪

20:49.061 --> 20:50.827
Stay tuned, Harold.

20:50.829 --> 20:54.364
♪

20:54.366 --> 20:56.433
[keypad beeping]

20:56.435 --> 21:04.306
♪

21:10.681 --> 21:14.083
(Greer) Everything we have
worked for is coming to fruition.

21:14.085 --> 21:17.253
The Correction is upon us.

21:17.255 --> 21:19.088
Standby for instructions.

21:19.090 --> 21:23.926
♪

21:23.928 --> 21:26.128
You need to leave, Harold. Now.

21:26.130 --> 21:27.696
Not without you, Ms. Groves.

21:27.698 --> 21:29.065
(Root) You don't have a choice.

21:29.067 --> 21:31.867
This is Samaritan's base of operations.

21:31.869 --> 21:34.069
We're in the belly of the beast.

21:46.901 --> 21:49.969
[tense music]

21:49.971 --> 21:54.974
♪

21:54.976 --> 21:57.676
You have to shut your eyes.

21:57.678 --> 22:01.713
A lesson I've learned all too well.

22:01.715 --> 22:04.016
I would've stayed in the dark too

22:04.018 --> 22:05.817
if some...

22:05.819 --> 22:07.386
[sighs]

22:07.388 --> 22:11.556
Friends hadn't convinced
me to dig a little deeper.

22:11.558 --> 22:14.192
♪

22:14.194 --> 22:16.427
Now, I'm curious.

22:16.429 --> 22:19.898
How does a prep school girl from Greenwich

22:19.900 --> 22:23.668
ever come to work for Samaritan?

22:23.670 --> 22:26.872
I... I have no idea

22:26.874 --> 22:29.773
who this Samaritan is.

22:29.775 --> 22:32.443
This is all a huge mistake.

22:32.445 --> 22:34.178
Please...

22:34.180 --> 22:36.180
please, I...

22:36.182 --> 22:38.849
I have a daughter.

22:38.851 --> 22:41.019
Sarah. She's a toddler.

22:41.021 --> 22:43.187
And my son, Jackson, he's
just starting second grade.

22:43.189 --> 22:45.623
I just want to go home

22:45.625 --> 22:48.379
and see them.

22:49.128 --> 22:52.563
♪

22:52.565 --> 22:55.399
I'm sorry.

22:55.401 --> 22:57.134
I know how you feel.

22:57.136 --> 23:00.971
I lost my mother too at a very young age.

23:00.973 --> 23:02.472
♪

23:02.474 --> 23:04.574
But you already know
that, don't you, Shelly?

23:04.576 --> 23:07.377
That's why you keep
playing the mother card.

23:07.379 --> 23:11.214
Did it tell you to do that?

23:11.216 --> 23:13.816
Did it think

23:13.818 --> 23:18.087
that you could handle me too?

23:18.089 --> 23:20.790
How many agents are you
handling for Samaritan?

23:20.792 --> 23:28.064
♪

23:29.199 --> 23:32.234
You recognize anyone?

23:32.236 --> 23:35.904
(Control) Kind of looks like Tyler.

23:35.906 --> 23:37.406
At least it used to.

23:37.408 --> 23:40.142
I go... I go to the park on my lunch hour.

23:40.144 --> 23:42.078
I like to watch the artists paint.

23:42.080 --> 23:45.681
Who do you watch in the coffee shop?

23:45.683 --> 23:48.517
I'm in that coffee shop at
least three times a week.

23:48.519 --> 23:50.018
Okay, this is just...

23:50.020 --> 23:51.853
this is just some sort
of freak coincidence.

23:51.855 --> 23:54.690
A more pertinent question would be,

23:54.692 --> 23:57.826
what's a middle-aged,
caffeine-addicted school teacher

23:57.828 --> 24:01.429
doing roaming the halls of the White House?

24:01.431 --> 24:09.270
♪

24:13.709 --> 24:16.877
You have no idea what's
coming for you, bitch.

24:16.879 --> 24:19.614
♪

24:24.152 --> 24:26.553
(Dominic) I'm offering
a place at the table.

24:26.555 --> 24:29.890
Acknowledge me as the
head of the five families,

24:29.892 --> 24:32.059
and you and your men can live.

24:32.061 --> 24:33.661
Just because you're sitting at the head

24:33.663 --> 24:35.195
doesn't mean you can lead.

24:35.197 --> 24:36.831
My men are loyal to me.

24:36.833 --> 24:38.499
Which men?

24:38.501 --> 24:42.302
The Cosa Nostra or our boys in blue?

24:42.304 --> 24:46.706
Ah, and then there's the
mysterious third party...

24:46.708 --> 24:47.974
the guy with the tech.

24:47.976 --> 24:49.343
The hacker.

24:49.345 --> 24:50.744
(Harper) Don't bother lying.

24:50.746 --> 24:52.812
I told them about Harold.

24:52.814 --> 24:54.080
Honest about your deceit.

24:54.082 --> 24:56.650
How noble.

24:56.652 --> 25:01.187
Harold's tapped into the city's cameras.

25:01.189 --> 25:03.556
I want his system.

25:03.558 --> 25:05.258
Well, you're gonna kill me regardless.

25:05.260 --> 25:06.660
Why turn on a friend?

25:06.662 --> 25:10.530
Like you turned on your right-hand man?

25:10.532 --> 25:14.267
Anthony, right?

25:14.269 --> 25:16.835
How's it feel knowing you're responsible

25:16.837 --> 25:20.239
for your friend's death?

25:20.241 --> 25:22.341
Do you really want to know?

25:22.343 --> 25:25.278
[tense music]

25:25.280 --> 25:28.247
Be careful what you wish for, Dominic.

25:28.249 --> 25:36.121
♪

25:38.124 --> 25:42.427
We'll start with the
hand and work our way up.

25:42.429 --> 25:45.397
♪

25:45.399 --> 25:46.798
[hammer thuds] [Elias screams]

25:46.800 --> 25:48.366
Where do you meet Harold?

25:48.368 --> 25:50.635
Do you have a safe house in the city?

25:50.637 --> 25:57.742
♪

25:57.744 --> 25:59.444
If I knew, I would've told you by now.

25:59.446 --> 26:02.280
♪

26:02.282 --> 26:08.086
Where is your boss, Detective?

26:08.088 --> 26:11.555
Truth is,

26:11.557 --> 26:14.092
I don't know.

26:14.094 --> 26:17.895
The truth hurts.

26:17.897 --> 26:20.631
[gurgling]

26:20.633 --> 26:21.832
You want some air?

26:21.834 --> 26:24.501
Tell me where your hacker boss is.

26:24.503 --> 26:26.036
[coughs]

26:26.038 --> 26:27.304
[groans]

26:27.306 --> 26:28.606
- Again.
- Wait.

26:28.608 --> 26:30.173
Wait. [coughs]

26:30.175 --> 26:31.742
Wait.

26:31.744 --> 26:33.844
You got... you got a loofah?

26:33.846 --> 26:36.246
Maybe you can wash my
back while you're at it.

26:36.248 --> 26:44.121
♪

26:46.791 --> 26:48.959
[gurgling]

26:48.961 --> 26:50.260
[door squeaks]

26:50.262 --> 26:53.829
♪

26:53.831 --> 26:58.301
Found this in one of the canisters.

26:58.303 --> 27:00.770
Date and time of the courthouse hearing.

27:00.772 --> 27:02.305
Got a rat in our crew.

27:02.307 --> 27:04.440
He got our boys killed.

27:04.442 --> 27:06.942
An inside man selling secrets to Elias.

27:06.944 --> 27:09.311
♪

27:09.313 --> 27:11.013
[gurgling]

27:11.015 --> 27:18.620
♪

27:18.622 --> 27:20.389
Fish him out. We got
more important business.

27:20.391 --> 27:22.557
[gasping]

27:22.559 --> 27:23.893
(Link) Come help me out.

27:23.895 --> 27:26.194
♪

27:26.196 --> 27:27.462
I'll go get the key.

27:27.464 --> 27:29.498
[groans]

27:29.500 --> 27:32.233
Listen, I got a little text from Thornhill.

27:32.235 --> 27:34.636
She said I could name my
price if I save your ass.

27:34.638 --> 27:36.137
[coughs]

27:36.139 --> 27:37.506
[handcuffs jingle, lock clicks]

27:37.508 --> 27:40.709
Hey, thanks for the spa day, sunshine.

27:40.711 --> 27:41.976
I'm not done with you yet.

27:41.978 --> 27:43.577
[grunts] [handcuffs jingle]

27:43.579 --> 27:44.913
[coughs]

27:44.915 --> 27:52.787
♪

27:55.257 --> 27:58.092
This is a restricted floor, Doctor.

27:58.094 --> 27:59.427
Sorry.

27:59.429 --> 28:02.496
I was looking for an aspirin stash.

28:02.498 --> 28:04.164
I have a lower back thing.

28:04.166 --> 28:06.033
[gunshots ping] [men grunt]

28:06.035 --> 28:07.568
[men groaning]

28:07.570 --> 28:11.572
♪

28:11.574 --> 28:12.973
Sameen?

28:13.288 --> 28:15.555
_

28:15.585 --> 28:18.497
♪

28:18.788 --> 28:21.000
_

28:28.522 --> 28:29.589
[metallic clang]

28:29.591 --> 28:37.063
♪

28:38.198 --> 28:40.533
You just missed her.

28:40.535 --> 28:41.835
[gunshots ping]

28:41.837 --> 28:44.203
♪

28:44.205 --> 28:45.705
[gunshot pings]

28:45.707 --> 28:47.707
Aah!

28:47.709 --> 28:49.208
[gunshots]

28:49.210 --> 28:50.209
[grunting]

28:50.211 --> 28:53.212
[gun clicks]

28:53.214 --> 28:55.882
[gun clatters on floor]

28:55.884 --> 28:57.984
Time to finish what we started.

28:57.986 --> 29:00.719
You read my mind.

29:00.721 --> 29:03.789
[both grunting]

29:03.791 --> 29:06.592
♪

29:06.594 --> 29:08.460
Where are they taking her?

29:08.462 --> 29:11.497
Relax. I'm sure it's someplace nice.

29:11.499 --> 29:13.599
♪ ♪

29:13.601 --> 29:15.333
[Root grunting]

29:15.335 --> 29:17.903
(Martine) You should be proud of Shaw.

29:17.905 --> 29:20.572
She held out for a month or two.

29:20.574 --> 29:22.340
I had to hurt her pretty bad.

29:22.342 --> 29:24.075
[gasps, groans]

29:24.077 --> 29:27.279
But she broke eventually.

29:27.281 --> 29:29.147
Lying bitch.

29:29.149 --> 29:31.416
And by the way, thanks

29:31.418 --> 29:33.418
for doing everything she said you would do.

29:33.420 --> 29:36.487
[solemn music]

29:36.489 --> 29:39.099
♪

29:39.600 --> 29:40.900
_

29:43.095 --> 29:46.195
You're calmer than normal, John,

29:46.197 --> 29:49.466
given the circumstances.

29:49.468 --> 29:52.869
I took a trip to the mountains,

29:52.871 --> 29:54.270
and I saw an old friend.

29:54.272 --> 29:58.341
♪

29:58.343 --> 30:00.776
Just reminded me what I've been missing.

30:00.778 --> 30:04.347
And what is that?

30:04.349 --> 30:05.915
Life.

30:05.917 --> 30:07.850
And yet, here you are,

30:07.852 --> 30:11.854
stuck in a dark basement with me.

30:11.856 --> 30:14.490
You should have heeded my warning.

30:14.492 --> 30:18.961
You knew that the Brotherhood was coming.

30:18.963 --> 30:22.531
That canister in the trash...

30:22.533 --> 30:24.467
that wasn't a mistake.

30:24.469 --> 30:26.401
Did I leave a bread crumb?

30:26.403 --> 30:27.970
Just wondering what's up your sleeve.

30:27.972 --> 30:29.972
Trap door?

30:29.974 --> 30:32.641
Pneumatic tubes rigged with C-4?

30:32.643 --> 30:35.310
I'm afraid this is my last stand.

30:35.312 --> 30:40.182
♪

30:40.184 --> 30:43.385
You're an honorable man, John.

30:43.387 --> 30:46.188
It's been nice knowing you.

30:46.190 --> 30:47.589
[door clicks]

30:47.591 --> 30:51.392
Gonna need you to write a little letter.

30:51.394 --> 30:52.827
With your good hand.

30:52.829 --> 30:56.998
At "Sunrise, 3648 Lafayette Avenue."

30:57.000 --> 30:58.666
[tense music]

30:58.668 --> 31:00.935
Unless you want Riley here
to wipe for you from now on.

31:00.937 --> 31:04.038
How 'bout you come a little closer?

31:04.040 --> 31:06.540
I'll settle my own score, John.

31:06.542 --> 31:08.509
My friends are upset
because they're discovered

31:08.511 --> 31:10.111
a traitor in their midst.

31:10.113 --> 31:12.213
Now write,

31:12.215 --> 31:14.081
"Veni, vidi, vici."

31:14.083 --> 31:21.955
♪

31:24.225 --> 31:25.893
It's the address to the Brotherhood's

31:25.895 --> 31:27.127
base of operations.

31:27.129 --> 31:28.629
As far as your men are concerned,

31:28.631 --> 31:30.964
their boss just gave them orders to invade.

31:30.966 --> 31:33.066
And when they come, the
Brotherhood will be waiting.

31:33.068 --> 31:35.101
(Dominic) Your men can die by your hands

31:35.103 --> 31:38.438
or you can give me the
name of the rat in my crew.

31:38.440 --> 31:40.140
♪

31:43.777 --> 31:45.545
(Martine) Let's get
her strapped to the bed.

31:45.547 --> 31:47.414
This shouldn't take long.

31:47.416 --> 31:49.482
[dramatic music]

31:49.484 --> 31:52.419
[grunting]

31:54.655 --> 31:56.155
(Greer) Really, Ms. Groves.

31:56.157 --> 32:00.225
There's such a thing as nobility in defeat.

32:00.227 --> 32:03.162
I have everything I
need to find the Machine,

32:03.164 --> 32:05.264
and no amount of kicking will change that.

32:05.266 --> 32:08.568
If you found the Machine,
I'd be the first to know.

32:08.570 --> 32:09.735
(Greer) Exactly.

32:09.737 --> 32:12.237
We have scoured every network device

32:12.239 --> 32:14.106
on the planet without success,

32:14.108 --> 32:18.277
until I realized, you are
the last piece of the puzzle.

32:18.279 --> 32:19.945
The answer is in your head.

32:19.947 --> 32:21.280
[chuckles]

32:21.282 --> 32:23.182
I don't have the slightest idea

32:23.184 --> 32:24.616
where the Machine's located.

32:24.618 --> 32:26.251
Not in your brain.

32:26.253 --> 32:27.752
In your head.

32:27.754 --> 32:30.922
Your direct line to the Machine.

32:30.924 --> 32:33.625
The cochlear implant.

32:33.627 --> 32:36.260
Your little girlfriend
told us all about it.

32:36.262 --> 32:38.129
She would never.

32:38.131 --> 32:40.131
(Greer) We have no reason to
lie about something like that.

32:40.133 --> 32:41.633
[tense music]

32:41.635 --> 32:44.936
(Greer) Welcome, Mr. Finch.

32:44.938 --> 32:47.972
You're just in time to see us
cut your friend's head open.

32:47.974 --> 32:49.607
There'll be some brain damage,

32:49.609 --> 32:52.376
but you'll still be able to
clothe and feed yourself.

32:52.378 --> 32:56.947
Though I can't say you'll be
much a marksman moving forward.

32:56.949 --> 33:00.218
♪

33:00.220 --> 33:04.187
[saw whirring]

33:04.189 --> 33:06.624
Harold doesn't have to see this.

33:06.626 --> 33:11.294
If you want, I'll end him
first and let you watch.

33:11.296 --> 33:15.666
Lay a hand on him, I'll kill you.

33:15.668 --> 33:18.668
Sit back. Relax, honey.

33:18.670 --> 33:22.705
Or I'll lay more than just a hand on him.

33:22.707 --> 33:25.208
♪

33:25.210 --> 33:29.412
He doesn't look like much of a fighter.

33:29.414 --> 33:31.981
Bet he'll died without so much as a peep.

33:31.983 --> 33:34.417
♪

33:34.419 --> 33:36.819
[dramatic music]

33:36.821 --> 33:38.387
[neck snaps]

33:38.389 --> 33:41.323
♪

33:41.325 --> 33:42.558
What do you know?

33:42.560 --> 33:46.863
Not a peep.

33:46.865 --> 33:49.132
Now I surrender.

33:59.895 --> 34:01.493
_

34:01.585 --> 34:03.354
[tense music]

34:03.356 --> 34:05.588
♪

34:05.590 --> 34:08.725
Who's your contact at the White House?

34:08.726 --> 34:11.360
I used to admire you...

34:11.362 --> 34:15.866
the work you did for your country.

34:15.868 --> 34:18.701
You could still prove
that you're a true patriot.

34:18.703 --> 34:20.203
[chuckles softly]

34:20.205 --> 34:23.306
How? By letting you go?

34:23.308 --> 34:27.042
No, this is not about me.

34:27.043 --> 34:29.712
It's about to begin.

34:29.714 --> 34:32.315
The Correction.

34:32.317 --> 34:34.484
Correction?

34:34.485 --> 34:35.551
For whom?

34:35.553 --> 34:37.052
Don't worry.

34:37.054 --> 34:38.754
It's nothing you haven't done yourself.

34:38.755 --> 34:40.755
What are you talking about?

34:40.757 --> 34:42.591
The ferry bombing.

34:42.592 --> 34:45.327
You sanctioned Nathan Ingram's death

34:45.329 --> 34:49.731
along with all the other innocent people.

34:49.733 --> 34:51.466
Samaritan is planning an attack.

34:51.467 --> 34:52.935
Attack?

34:52.937 --> 34:54.835
Is that you would classify
the actions you took

34:54.838 --> 34:57.472
to protect your country?

34:57.474 --> 35:00.509
When?

35:00.511 --> 35:08.383
♪

35:08.966 --> 35:10.584
_

35:13.856 --> 35:15.489
May 6th.

35:15.491 --> 35:19.794
♪

35:19.796 --> 35:23.832
What does that number mean?

35:23.834 --> 35:25.099
[gun cocks]

35:25.101 --> 35:26.100
You can go ahead and shoot me.

35:26.102 --> 35:29.370
I'm not gonna tell you.

35:29.372 --> 35:30.938
- [grunts]
- Aah!

35:30.940 --> 35:34.942
[gasping]

35:34.944 --> 35:36.711
You should save your energy,

35:36.713 --> 35:39.547
because you're gonna need it.

35:39.549 --> 35:42.216
(Sherry) Do you know the
story of Sodom and Gomorrah?

35:42.218 --> 35:47.354
Lot's wife couldn't help but
look back at the burning city,

35:47.356 --> 35:50.623
and she burst into a pillar of salt.

35:50.625 --> 35:53.961
But you can still save yourself

35:53.963 --> 35:58.365
if you don't do anything
to stop the Correction.

35:58.367 --> 36:01.401
You said yourself, you're
good at shutting your eyes.

36:01.403 --> 36:06.472
Well, the world is about to catch fire.

36:06.474 --> 36:09.041
Here's your last chance to look away.

36:09.043 --> 36:11.911
♪

36:18.418 --> 36:20.253
[tense music]

36:20.255 --> 36:22.154
Time's up.

36:22.156 --> 36:23.722
Do we have an agreement,

36:23.724 --> 36:27.092
or do we send the note and
exterminate your men?

36:27.094 --> 36:29.160
♪

36:29.162 --> 36:30.496
Send it through the tubes.

36:30.498 --> 36:33.198
Okay, okay. You win.

36:33.200 --> 36:37.202
Just please... just leave my men alone.

36:37.204 --> 36:39.670
Now tell me,

36:39.672 --> 36:41.506
who's your informant?

36:41.508 --> 36:46.444
♪

36:46.446 --> 36:51.182
He has me send payments to this account.

36:51.184 --> 36:53.919
Your money man can verify.

36:53.921 --> 36:58.623
♪

36:58.625 --> 36:59.924
[camera shutter snaps]

36:59.926 --> 37:02.593
We'll be hearing shortly.

37:02.595 --> 37:05.863
♪

37:05.865 --> 37:07.264
[phone rings]

37:07.266 --> 37:09.700
Yeah, Lawrence. What do you got?

37:09.702 --> 37:17.574
♪

37:19.144 --> 37:21.778
No, that'll be all.

37:21.780 --> 37:28.085
♪

37:28.087 --> 37:29.385
Lawrence give you a name?

37:29.387 --> 37:32.388
An alias.

37:32.390 --> 37:35.124
I need your advice on
how to deal with this.

37:35.126 --> 37:37.994
It's not enough to hit back.

37:37.996 --> 37:40.464
Got to put your enemy in the ground.

37:40.466 --> 37:42.966
♪

37:42.968 --> 37:45.335
Whose name was on the account?

37:45.337 --> 37:48.271
[gunshots]

37:49.974 --> 37:53.009
It was yours, Link.

37:53.011 --> 37:56.745
[laughing]

37:56.747 --> 37:59.983
Oh. Oh, man.

37:59.985 --> 38:02.651
You could take my title, but
you can't hold on to it.

38:02.653 --> 38:05.187
You can't trust anyone.

38:05.189 --> 38:07.255
And now your men won't trust you.

38:07.257 --> 38:11.861
They trust that I will exterminate a rat.

38:11.863 --> 38:13.295
Rat?

38:13.297 --> 38:16.225
I might have lied about a few things.

38:16.345 --> 38:18.500
Like the message your men intercepted.

38:18.502 --> 38:23.138
♪

38:23.140 --> 38:27.042
You planted that message?

38:27.044 --> 38:28.310
You knew we were coming.

38:28.312 --> 38:29.160
Well, good news,

38:29.280 --> 38:30.639
there's no rat in your organization.

38:30.759 --> 38:34.016
Bad new, you need a new right-hand man.

38:34.018 --> 38:35.282
[grunting]

38:35.284 --> 38:36.551
You want to kill me? Go ahead.

38:36.553 --> 38:39.721
You were always gonna win this war anyway.

38:39.723 --> 38:42.456
(Reese) Kill him, you'll never
get the information you want.

38:42.458 --> 38:44.626
Tell me you have another plan, Elias.

38:44.628 --> 38:45.755
This is my plan, John.

38:45.875 --> 38:47.342
I told you I'd make
them answer for Anthony.

38:47.344 --> 38:49.877
So tell me, how does it feel knowing

38:49.879 --> 38:52.613
that you're responsible
for your friend's death?

38:52.615 --> 38:59.120
♪

39:02.290 --> 39:05.359
[tense music]

39:05.361 --> 39:07.694
♪

39:07.696 --> 39:09.696
Shall we continue?

39:09.698 --> 39:12.031
Have you forgotten her so quickly?

39:12.033 --> 39:14.901
You've already discarded her,
and you're a human being.

39:14.903 --> 39:17.170
Imagine how quickly that
thing that you've created

39:17.172 --> 39:18.972
would discard you.

39:18.974 --> 39:20.774
Do you ever lay awake at night wondering

39:20.776 --> 39:23.143
if one day it will see <i>you</i> as a threat?

39:23.145 --> 39:25.311
Or worse, as irrelevant?

39:25.313 --> 39:26.780
How arrogant of you to think

39:26.782 --> 39:31.484
that any of us are anything but irrelevant.

39:31.486 --> 39:34.417
♪

39:34.418 --> 39:39.418
_

39:39.427 --> 39:42.628
Samaritan is offering your
Machine a second chance

39:42.630 --> 39:45.498
to save the lives of its human agents.

39:45.500 --> 39:47.966
Give up its location,

39:47.968 --> 39:49.568
or they die.

39:49.570 --> 39:53.238
The offer expires in 60 seconds.

39:53.240 --> 39:59.744
♪

39:59.746 --> 40:04.683
[bone saw buzzing]

40:04.685 --> 40:06.018
Don't do it.

40:06.020 --> 40:07.619
Please.

40:07.621 --> 40:11.456
Don't give yourself up.

40:11.458 --> 40:12.791
Harold was right.

40:12.793 --> 40:16.994
We are interchangeable.

40:16.996 --> 40:18.262
You can replace us.

40:18.264 --> 40:21.265
You can keep fighting.

40:21.267 --> 40:23.868
[electronics powering down]

40:23.870 --> 40:26.705
[solemn music]

40:26.707 --> 40:29.541
[electronics beeping]

40:29.543 --> 40:34.537
♪

40:35.899 --> 40:37.238
_

40:41.000 --> 40:43.000
_

40:47.691 --> 40:49.001
_

40:51.840 --> 40:53.502
_

40:57.635 --> 41:01.004
No, don't do it.

41:01.006 --> 41:03.539
Don't die for us.

41:03.541 --> 41:04.000
♪

41:04.100 --> 41:05.100
_

41:06.150 --> 41:07.600
_

41:08.222 --> 41:09.131
_

41:09.555 --> 41:11.666
_

41:21.399 --> 41:23.161
_

41:23.494 --> 41:26.929
[electronics click, whir]

41:26.931 --> 41:29.665
♪ ♪

41:29.667 --> 41:33.469
Until the next time, Mr. Finch.

41:33.471 --> 41:35.488
[tense music]

41:35.499 --> 41:37.299
_

41:37.334 --> 41:44.413
♪ ♪

41:44.415 --> 41:47.349
(Shelly) Go home to your loved ones.

41:47.351 --> 41:49.451
Hold your daughter tight,

41:49.453 --> 41:52.388
because a new day is dawning.

41:52.390 --> 41:55.123
And those who impede progress...

41:55.125 --> 41:57.859
the disruptive, the aberrant...

41:57.861 --> 42:01.396
will be systematically
purged from our society.

42:01.398 --> 42:05.099
There will be no mercy,

42:05.101 --> 42:09.637
no stay of execution.

42:09.639 --> 42:13.908
For some, this will be the end.

42:13.910 --> 42:15.709
But for others,

42:15.711 --> 42:18.579
a rebirth.

42:18.581 --> 42:20.614
A second chance to live the life

42:20.616 --> 42:22.716
that they were designed for.

42:22.718 --> 42:25.986
Every life given a purpose.

42:25.988 --> 42:32.426
Samaritan will build a new world.

42:32.428 --> 42:34.995
A better world.

42:34.997 --> 42:37.498
Too bad you won't live to see it.

42:37.500 --> 42:39.667
♪ ♪

42:39.669 --> 42:42.569
[gunshots ping]

42:42.571 --> 42:48.808
♪

42:48.810 --> 42:51.511
The Machine gave up its
location to save our lives.

42:51.513 --> 42:55.082
They're going to kill her, Harold.

42:55.084 --> 42:56.483
Do you know where they're going?

42:56.485 --> 42:57.750
I don't know.

42:57.752 --> 42:59.452
But we have to get there first,

42:59.454 --> 43:01.788
before it's too late.

43:03.557 --> 43:06.165
♪

